meanings.definition: To surpass in skill or performance.
meanings.sent1: She was outstunting her classmates in math.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outstunted his previous record in the race.
meanings.sent3: The magician outstunted everyone with his amazing card tricks.
meanings.sent4: The singer outstunted all expectations with her powerful voice.
meanings.sent5: The chef outstunted himself by creating a new delicious dish.

meanings.definition: To outdo in a showy or ostentatious manner.
meanings.sent1: He was outstunting his friends with his flashy new car.
meanings.sent2: The dancer outstunted the others with her elaborate costume.
meanings.sent3: The peacock outstunted the other birds with its colorful feathers.
meanings.sent4: The actor outstunted his co-stars with his dramatic performance.
meanings.sent5: The artist outstunted the competition with her bold painting.
